Obviously since Ford
engineers designed it,

1402
01:25:29,295 --> 01:25:31,923
they had knowledge of it long before
their first meeting with Dr. Kearns...

1403
01:25:31,998 --> 01:25:34,626
Would you agree that Dr. Kearns
was the first person in the world,

1404
01:25:34,701 --> 01:25:36,430
to your knowledge,
to propose that combination?

1405
01:25:36,502 --> 01:25:40,336
I believe it's possible that
it was Motorola and Ranco.

1406
01:25:40,773 --> 01:25:41,899
They may have.
<i>The motor makes one</i>

1407
01:25:41,975 --> 01:25:45,035
<i>revolution to get one wipe out
of 360 degrees. It's very simple.</i>

1408
01:25:45,111 --> 01:25:46,510
<i>We worked on that</i>
<i>for two weeks.</i>

1409
01:25:46,579 --> 01:25:49,810
<i>Well, certainly it is important to
understand that within the Ford organization,</i>

1410
01:25:49,882 --> 01:25:51,213
<i>it takes some time</i>
<i>to get written...</i>

1411
01:25:51,284 --> 01:25:54,219
<i>Well, when you start the car,
the transistors come on automatically</i>

1412
01:25:54,287 --> 01:25:56,915
<i>and supply 50 times</i>
<i>as much current.</i>

1413
01:25:57,223 --> 01:26:01,353
To reiterate, you've worked in the
automobile industry for well over 20 years

1414
01:26:01,427 --> 01:26:05,295
and you've been an executive at the company
for a number of those years, correct?

1415
01:26:05,365 --> 01:26:06,957
That's correct.

1416
01:26:07,166 --> 01:26:11,500
Mr. Tyler, to be clear,
did you ever tell Mr. Kearns

1417
01:26:11,571 --> 01:26:14,802
that he had, quote,
"Won the wiper competition"?

1418
01:26:15,675 --> 01:26:20,703
It doesn't sound much like me, so, no, I
really don't recall making that comment.

1419
01:26:21,180 --> 01:26:24,240
I mean, I certainly tried to be encouraging
to Mr. Kearns. I respected the man.

1420
01:26:24,317 --> 01:26:27,809
